2022 has been the year that rocked my world and changed me in the most profound ways possible.  I started the year grieving the unexpected loss of my mom, and then in April, my dad died, also unexpectedly, right before my eyes. The grief, sadness and trauma from their deaths has completely overwhelmed me at times, and I have experienced darkness like I never thought imaginable.  While this has been the worst year of my life, there were still some bright moments that outshone the darkness. The highlight of my year was hands down being presented with the opportunity to travel to Israel. When I realized the trip fell on the one-year anniversary of my mom’s death, I knew it was a sign. Visiting Jerusalem and standing on the same ground where Jesus once walked was a surreal experience, and I knew there was no place on Earth where I could be closer to my parents than right there.  Lighting candles for each of them in the Church of the Holy Sepulchre and praying at The Wailing Wall are moments I will never forget, and I know without a doubt my parents were standing right beside me.  I will continue to honor their memories and do my best to make them proud until the day that I join them again for all of eternity (and I cannot wait for that day!). 

Thank you for allowing me to share this journey with you. Thank you for giving me grace and support. Thank you for making me feel comfortable enough to get on here and be raw and vulnerable.  The love you all have shown me over the past year has been humbling, and I am beyond grateful for this special community. 

I hope the new year brings you peace, comfort, good health and happiness ❤️

“How do you work out during your lunch break and go back to work after!?” I get asked this every time I post about a lunchtime workout. I’ve been working out at lunch for years and I have my routine down pat, but it isn’t rocket science, y’all!  First of all, I do not mess around when I’m in the gym at lunch - I waste no time and I usually never have a problem getting in and out in an hour (that’s another bonus to the @fasterwaytofatloss - the workouts truly cater to a woman’s busy lifestyle!). Here is a quick rundown of the “refresh necessities” I keep in my gym bag: 

•Bath Wipes - Trust me, I SWEAT…especially on cardio days!  But I don’t have enough time to shower, so bath wipes are my saving grace and work perfect for a quick clean-up/refresh to get me through the afternoon, then I shower when I get home at the end of the day. I have been using the same ones (from Amazon) for several years now and swear by them!  I’ll link them on LTK and in stories if you want to check them out. 
•Hand Towel, Deodorant, Perfume - the obvious things!
•Hair Oil - I keep this on hand to tame down the frizz and unruly hairs after wearing a ponytail and sweating 
•My makeup bag - I only touch up where I may have sweated. I don’t reapply a full face of makeup. 

And that’s it!  Seems so elementary, I’m sure, but these are the things I swear by when it comes to lunchtime workouts for the working girl!
